    <title>
        Fix HasMenuCurrent and IsDescendant/IsAncestor when comparing to itself
    </title>
    <updated>2022-05-28T08:56:54Z</updated>
    <media:thumbnail height="30" width="30" url="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/394382?s=30&amp;u=0c57f8445a153dbc0991ae3adaecab4f542ce17f&amp;v=4"/>
    <author>
      <name>bep</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/bep</uri>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;pre style=&#39;white-space:pre-wrap;width:81ex&#39;&gt;Fix HasMenuCurrent and IsDescendant/IsAncestor when comparing to itself

There may be sites in the wild that depends on the faulty behaviour of IsDescendant/IsAncestor when comparing to itself, but

* The documentation and common sense says that a thing cannot be descendant or ancestor to itself.
* The bug introduced in `HasMenuCurrent` comes directly from that confusion.

Fixes #9846&lt;/pre&gt;
    </content>
  </entry>
